column5: Anybody here in one of the 4 boats out there???
Great shots Wayne, I'm not in any of those boats but with a little luck maybe next week.
Wayne, it's starting to get a bit of it's greenish tingle back.  I assume you were down towards the mouth?  I wonder what it looks like up towards 89.

See pic # 1. Almost got myself in do do following creeks and not paying attention to where I was... almost overflew base Borden on my North bound flight!  Didn't take as many pics as I'd usually... wasn't my personal airplane... so not as comfortable "knee flying"..
Assuming there's no more rain, do you think it will be good to go come Saturday?
I don't know.. hasn't rained in well over a week and look at that silt outflow !! There's still lots of snow in the bush and even in drainage ditches in wide open farmers fields.
Glad to hear you made  it home ok.  Now the question is ...where you gonna put it ?  TB

Right where you parked your van yesterday.. have no choice.    Now what I'm gonna do with the floats from it after I pick them up tomorrow... or the other airplane coming in Saturday.. I have no idea. All I know is I'm never gonna get to the lake....
good, maybe you will be around for the beginning of muskie season
maybe stick those old cars of yours out under the trees ..its only bird crap!   LOL  tb
Check fire..check fire, aw jeez it's only Wayne buzzing around up there...lets air condition his wings..
